cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the development of neural network architectures for classification tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific application of the proposed framework is for age prediction in face images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the limitations of commonly used loss functions and proposes a new framework, which involves theoretical guarantees and optimization techniques, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the proposed method involves the use of face image datasets, which is a common application in natural language processing (cs.CL).
